article.headline: Colorado St. 80, Adams St. 55
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Colton Iverson and Dorian Green each scored 17 points and Colorado State rolled to an 80-55 victory over Adams State on Saturday. It was the 20th straight home win at Moby Arena for Colorado State (11-2). Greg Smith and Wes Eikmeier each scored 11 points for the Rams. Colorado State also had a 40-26 rebounding advantage, and outscored Adams State (7-1) 36-16 in the paint and 14-4 off turnovers. John Jackson led Adams State with 17 points, and Kaimyn Pruitt grabbed 10 rebounds. Adams State could only hit 29 percent of its field-goal attempts and was 6 of 16 from the free-throw line.
